cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper introduces a new neural network architecture for representing long sequences, which is a common problem in natural language processing and computer vision. The method uses a backbone 1 dimensional CNN to slice out random patches of the feature space and find a representation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on developing a new neural network architecture and benchmarking it on computer vision tasks.
